jjcoder
=======

jjcoder is an independent terminal coding agent. Its user interface — the
layout, the dark color palette, and the general look-and-feel — is modelled
on ggcoder by KenKai, part of the gg-framework project:

    gg-framework  (MIT License, Copyright (c) 2025 KenKai)
    https://github.com/KenKaiii/gg-framework

ggcoder is MIT-licensed. This project takes design inspiration from it and
reimplements the interface from scratch; no source files from gg-framework
are copied into jjcoder. We gratefully credit KenKai's work.

What is different here: jjcoder's backend is a single path — the Claude Agent
SDK driving the Claude Code CLI — authenticated with a Claude Pro/Max
subscription, rather than ggcoder's own multi-provider agent.
